criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Understand the Italian language;

          2. Informative consensus;

          3. To be between 18 and 48 years old;

          4. To be sure of their gestational age, included between 37 0/0 and 41 5/7 weeks;

          5. Single fetus pregnancy in cephalic position;

          6. CTG with normal frequency and variability, without cardiac acceleration for 10
             minutes, and with no uterine contractions.

        Excluding criteria:

          1. BMI before pregnancy more than 30 kg/m2, and at the end of pregnancy more than 35
             kg/m2;

          2. Uterine fibromatosis;

          3. Premature rupture of membranes or oligohydramnios;

          4. Fetal pathology (malformation or genetic syndromes);

          5. Infective illness contract in pregnancy (CMV, herpes virus, rubella, syphilis,
             toxoplasmosis);

          6. Anomalous CTG, or with contractions

          7. Gestational diabet with insulin therapy;

        7) Cholestasis of pregnancy; 8) Use of corticosteroids within the last hours; 9) Use of
        prostaglandins for cervical ripening, within the last hours.
